(42, 12, 33, 40, 6, 19, 21, 'treasure in the heavens that faileth not', 'Heavenly Treasures Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of laying up treasures in heaven rather than on earth. They highlight the impermanence of earthly possessions and the security of heavenly treasures.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 12, 33, 42, 16, 9, 9, 'treasure in the heavens', 'Connection of Treasures and Relationships', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of investing in eternal treasures rather than earthly wealth. Luke 12:33 speaks of providing for oneself ''a treasure in the heavens,'' while Luke 16:9 encourages using wealth to create lasting relationships that lead to ''everlasting habitations.''', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
